a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-2))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 5) (Im (-2))"
shows  "a - b = -2"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Simplify $(3-2i)-(5-2i)$. The final Answer is -2
 ### Proof
 $(3-2i)- (5-2i) = 3-2i -5+2i = (3-5) + (-2i+2i) = \boxed{-2}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-2))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 5) (Im (-2))"
shows  "a - b = -2"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
